            <div xml:id="KT397-kilavi">
                <p type="edition">varaiviṭai vaittu nīṅkun talaimakaṟkut tōḻi uraittatu. </p>


                <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by the confidante to HIM, who leaves [her],
                    after the time of marriage was fixed. </p>
            </div>

            <div xml:id="KT397">
                <lg type="edition">
                    <l> naṉaimutir ñāḻaṟ ciṉaimaru ṭiraḷvī</l>
                    <l> neytaṉ māmalarp peytal pōla</l>
                    <l> vūtai tūṟṟu muravunīrc cērppa</l>
                    <l> tāyuṭaṉ ṟalaikkuṅ kālaiyum vāyviṭ</l>
                    <l> ṭaṉṉā yeṉṉuṅ kuḻavi pōla</l>
                    <l> viṉṉā ceyiṉu miṉitutalai yaḷippiṉu</l>
                    <l> niṉvaraip piṉaḷeṉ ṟōḻi</l>
                    <l> taṉṉuṟu viḻumaṅ kaḷaiñarō vilaḷē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <l> O man from the coast of the strong water, where the cold wind spreads</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> the egg-like round blossoms of the Ñāḻal,</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> on which buds are ripening,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> on the big blossoms of the blue waterlily, as if raining:</l>
                    <l> like a child, which opens [its] mouth [and] calls “mummy”</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> even at a time, when the mother slaps [it] in quarrel,</l>
                    <l> whether you do what is unsweet or sweetly protect [her],</l>
                    <l> my friend [is] one with you as a border. </l>
                    <l> She doesn't have anyone to remove the distress she has.</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
